I,\, J
K
R
(I\cap J)K = IK\cap JK
R
\Bbb Z[x,y]
I = (x), J = (y), K = (x,y)
I \cap J = (xy), \quad (I \cap J)K = (x^2y,xy^2)
IK = (x^2,xy), \quad JK = (xy,y^2),\quad IK \cap JK = (xy)
I \cap J\subseteq I,J
(I\cap J)K \subseteq IK, JK
(I \cap J)K \subseteq IK\cap JK
R = k[x,y,z,w]
I = (x,y)
J = (z,w)
K = (x,z)
I \cap J = (xw,xz,yz,yw)
(I \cap J)K = (x^2w,x^2z,xyz,xyw,zxw,xz^2,yz^2,yzw)
IK = (x^2,xy,xz,yz)
JK = (zx,xw,z^2,wz)
zx \in IK \cap JK.
(I \cap J)K
(I \cap J)K = IK \cap JK
